headlines.description: Jayson Tatum hit a fallaway as Blake Griffin stumbled with 2.9 seconds left, then tied up the Detroit veteran on the other end to help the Boston Celtics beat the Pistons 122-120 on Sunday for a weekend split.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum lifts Celtics past Pistons for weekend split

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal had 27 points, 10 rebounds and the assist on Thomas Bryant's go-ahead dunk with 14.9 seconds left, leading the Washington Wizards to a 123-122 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards edge Nets 123-122 after Irving, Durant miss late

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 22 points, 13 rebounds and eight assists, Anthony Davis added 17 points and nine rebounds and the Los Angeles Lakers opened a two-game set in Memphis with a 108-94 victory over the Grizzlies on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James leads Lakers past Grizzlies to open 2-game set

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored a season-high 36 points, Nikola Jokic had 19 points, 12 rebounds and 12 assists for is fourth triple-double of the season and the Denver Nuggets beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 124-109 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Jokic lead Nuggets past Timberwolves, 124-109

events.name: Utah Jazz at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine had 39 points and Coby White scored 21 of his 23 points in the second half to lead the Chicago Bulls to a 118-108 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 39, Bulls beat Doncic-less Mavericks 118-108

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 39 points and the Los Angeles Clippers held on to beat the Phoenix Suns 112-107 on Sunday night after nearly blowing a 31-point lead in a matchup of two of the Western Conference's top early season teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: George scores 39 points, Clippers hold off Suns 112-107

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry let it fly from way out under pressure with a minute-plus left for another perfect swish on the way to a career-high 62 points, and the Golden State Warriors beat Portland 137-122 on Sunday night to split the two-game set with the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry has career-high 62, Warriors beat Blazers
